<P>Out of this &s;tory he formed a tragedy, which, if
the circum&s;tances in which he wrote it be con&s;idered,
will afford at once an uncommon proof of &s;trength
of genius, and evenne&s;s of mind, of a &s;erenity not
$word$ be ru$$$ed, and an imagination not to be $word$</P>
<P><PB N="xx" REF="25">
During a con&s;iderable part of the time, in which
his was employed upon this performance, he was
without lodging, and often without meat; nor had
he any other conveniences for &s;tudy than the fields
