<P>He had indeed in Mr. Hill another critic of a
very different cla&s;s, from who&s;e friend&s;hip he re|received
great a&s;&s;i&s;tance on many occa&s;ions, and
whom he never mentioned but with the utmo&s;t ten|derne&s;s
